phonic-hiragana
written by Ken Goudsward, November 2010
released under creative commons licence attrib non-commercial share-alike

phonic-hiragana is 'sort of' a translator
you type or copy in phonetic spellings of japanese words such as "konichiwa", and you get back the proper hiragana 'spelling' click to edit

REQUIRES:
ruby, gem, shoes

version 1.0
works
single file includes program and 'translation logic'

version 2.0
not yet functional
it will feature the hash table split out into a library file separate from the programmatic function
feel free to fork the repo and make it work
